{
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we pioneer the exploration of scaling unified MLLMs with the MoE architecture and present an efficient MLLM named Uni-MoE that can leverage sparse MoE to adeptly manage and interpret multiple modalities.",
    "Specifically, as depicted in Figure 1, we first use modality-specific encoders to obtain the encoding of different modalities and map them into the language representation space of LLMs by the designed various connectors.",
    "They contain a trainable transformer model with subsequent linear projection layers to distil and project the output representations of frozen encoders, respectively.",
    "Then, we introduce a sparse MoE layer within the internal blocks of dense LLM.",
    "Hence, each MoE-based block features a shared self-attention layer applicable across all modalities, diverse experts based on feed-forward networks (FFN), and a sparse router for allocating token-level expertise."
  ]
}